erator that provides mobile voice and data services. iTalk is a cellular service provider that contracts with consumers and corporate customers directly for the provision of MTN airtime, handsets and related products. iTalk entered into a service provider 
agreement}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s8\cf0\sl240\slmult1\qj\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch {\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\fs18\lang7177\loch\f2\fs18\lang7177 iTalk used to be an exclusive service provider to MTN but the exclusivity in the iTalk/MTN Service Provision Agreement expired on 13 March 2003. Therefore while currently iTalk only sells MTN services, it is a non-exclusive independent service provider an
